args: ...So now you've come to me for advice.
*nod* D-do you really think they\nshould, um...elope?
If that's what the two of 'em want,\nwho am I to say otherwise?
You only get one thing from sticking your\nnose into other folks' romances: trouble.
Yup. And with THAT squared away...

Noelle, don't you think invading a noble's
manor is a little over the top? Or a LOT?
One wrong step, and we've got a
diplomatic crisis on our hands.
I know it's wrong. I knew it while I was\ndoing it. But I just... Um...
You felt there was justification for\ngoing over the top like that?
Well, now that you've pulled off your crazy\nstunt and gotten dragged even deeper into it,\ndo you regret anything?
Any thoughts about how maybe you\nshouldn't have gotten involved?
N-no! I don't think that at all!
Didn't think so. So what makes you think\nthe two of them feel any different?
I don't see them regretting their decision,\nno matter what happens after they elope.
They have a reason to shoot for the moon,\nso they'll find a way to live with the result.
I expect they'll still be thankful for your\nhelping them, too.
Nobody can say whether the future\nholds happiness or sorrow.
But I'm pretty sure a present where two\npeople in love can't be with one another\nis likely to be the latter.
That's why you agreed to help, right?
Thank you, Joachim. I feel like the knot\nin my chest is...gone.
I want to help Julia and Remuel\nstay connected for good!
I want to change their unhappy present!
Sounds like you've got your answer, then.
Just try to wrap this up quick, yeah?\nWe're supposed to head back soon.
Oh, and try not to start any wars.
Okay, I've got clothes, food, and money.\nThat's all a girl needs to elope, right?
Oh! I almost forgot Remuel's letter!
I would never forgive myself if I left\nhis beautiful words behind.
I'll treasure this all my life, for it is the\nprecious seed from which our happy future\nis sure to grow!
Heh. I really do owe Noelle a huge\ndebt for all she's—
Julia, my dear, I wanted to speak with\nyou about the upcoming—
Hmm? What did you put behind your back?
I, um...don't know what you mean?
And why is your bag packed? I don't\nremember you having a trip planned.
What, this? Noooo, this isn't my bag!\nIt's...um...
You are acting very strange, child.\nJust what are you...?
Show me what you're hiding this instant!
A letter? What in blazes is...?
...Remuel?! Love?! ELOPEMENT?!\nExplain this letter at once!
I'm sorry, Father, but I love him! I do!
I am aware that you believe as much.\nHowever, I am more curious how a letter\nfrom that dog found its way in here!
Was it the butler? Did you enlist a maid?\nBy Ilia, I'll have the entire staff sacked\nbefore the sun crosses the horizon!
STOP! It wasn't anyone from the manor!
N-no! Listen to me, Father, there isn't—

Stay your words, girl! I'm doubling the
guard at your door—no, TRIPLING it!
By the time I'm done, not even AIR will
be able to get in here without my say-so!
What have I done? How will Remuel\nand I ever be together now?
Oh, and poor Noelle! When she comes\nback with Remuel's reply, she'll be caught\nred-handed for sure!
